Iranian students are ready to die for their country’s nuclear program.
They created a human shield
A few hundred high school students have created a human shield around a nuclear site in Iran.
They want to support their country’s nuclear program in the face of a possible Israeli assault.
Students began praying at noon in front of the site and then wished the death of the US and Israel.
A few hundred students from the universities of Isfahan created a human shield Tuesday around the nuclear technology center of Isfahan where uranium is processed.
They thus openly expressed that they would defend their country's nuclear programme at the risk of their own lives.
The International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) noted in its latest report that Iran has continued to strengthen its nuclear weapons.
There are reports in Israel of a possible attack on Iranian nuclear facilities.
