The diet of an obese child: does not take breakfast and takes cold cuts for dinner
More than a third of children ages 9 to 13 have problems with overweight, 9% of schoolchildren will be above average weight and 5% are obese.
As current research shows, obese children come from families that have unhealthy lifestyles.
This shows again how important the environment in which the human being evolves and the models that surround him is.
On the tables of obese children, for example, we find charcuterie 50% more often than in the families of children with normal weight.
19% of obese people had French fries at dinner according to the survey conducted with an awareness-raising action "Obesity is not a coincidence"
In the families of the fat little ones sport is also not a habit, which is now the case of most schoolchildren today - only 15% replied that at least once a week parents found time for active movement.
A survey of 900 children
The survey was conducted during the last school year and involved 900 primary school students in the Czech Republic.
This was the second edition of "Obesity is not a coincidence", an action supported by the General Health Insurance and the Unilever company.
Since the beginning, more than 12,000 students from the sixth to the third year have enrolled in this project.
One of the determining factors that cause a dramatic increase in the number of overweight or even obese children is the absence of proper nutrition and insufficient physical exercise.
"Only half of the children surveyed say they eat breakfast five times a day - in case - lunch - snack - dinner, which is one of the basic principles of good nutrition," says one of the results of the survey.
No breakfast and cold cuts at dinner
Specialists draw attention to the fact that to have a healthy development you need some basic details such as a family breakfast at the same time.
In the Czech Republic, only 23% of student families eat at my same time.
In most families, everyone eats breakfast alone.
And the worst thing that has been noted is that one-tenth of the population does not eat breakfast at all.
Breakfast is the basis of a good daily diet.
The questionnaire showed that the families of obese children consumed unhealthy fries more often.
Almost every student - not to mention weight - drinks sugary drinks every day (70%).
More than 40% of the children questioned do sports regularly but for the parents it is half, only 15%.
Prepare Your Food
Another part of the survey allowed selected children (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to prepare their own food based on their own taste and personal opinion.
"The preferences of Czech children aged 12 to 15 are far from ideal in terms of healthy eating."
Among their favorite dishes there are many cakes, meats and sweets.
“The most alarming thing is a high preference for sweet lemonades,” the survey found.
For lunch it was the pasta that took the first place in front of the white meat.
The children did not want starch at all and the preference for fish and vegetable meals was very low.
Focus on health
The survey also showed that children are willing to change their habits from the moment they receive the ad hoc information.
"During a control of a group of survey participants who had completed the questionnaire after the 'Obesity is not a coincidence' awareness session, we witnessed a well-determined willingness to move towards healthy eating," the survey results indicate.
The most striking was for example with regard to sweet lemonades as children began to give preference to drinking water.
The children most often checked on the questionnaire white meat and fish as the main dish and would reduce the sweet dishes and the "knedliky" (Czech specialty of breadmeal or potatoes).
