The need for speed The Run is being fought across America.
Revision
Originally a run without problems is transformed because of a set of stupid mistakes of people who have nothing to do with it in a routine morning commute to work.
It fulfills to some extent everyone’s ambition but it is useless if no one wants to do anything more.
The new part subtitled The Run produced high expectations before its release.
It promised to take a new direction with the already old Need for Speed racing series and release a kind of game from the playable parts that would not only count with points.
So we were curious how the added passages will be where the main hero gets out of his car and does what he wants.
As is already being done in the NFS series, the result is completely different from what was expected.
These are potentially arcade racing games but the whole pulls down because of some unnecessary mistakes that have already existed for several years.
These are not really errors but rather the expression of an incomprehensible sloth on the part of the developers.
The adventure starts very well.
You are caught in the adventure whose main hero Jack has character problems and to solve them begins to participate in illegal races across America.
You sit behind the wheel on the west coast in San Francisco and your mission is to arrive first in New York.
The idea has interesting elements.
The route is divided into ten stages and then more than 50 races.
The result is that each race is done on a different route and the planned stages in different environments that are quite different from each other and are interesting.
The player does not feel for a single moment that the game offers him something identical.
Some environments are also pretty nice even if the graphical technical level is the same as the previous series.
It's not the end of the world.
But driving through the desert, in autumn landscapes or in highly snowy mountains is very visually enjoyable.
The tests are also occasionally embellished with an atypical element.
For example, in the desert you find yourself in a sandstorm that significantly decreases your visibility.
Then in the mountains you have to be careful that an avalanche does not fall on you.
In addition to this, the different races are well arranged one after the other.
There are only a few, but that is enough.
There are moments when you try to exceed the required number of opponents (as in a classic race) then you run against the clock (classic duel with the stopwatch) and then another duel with an opponent awaits you.
From time to time you also have the police who enter the game and try to make the situation difficult for you.
The novelty is the out-of-vehicle passages.
This is more of an interactive animation when Jack runs away in front of someone and you have to help him by hitting the right button at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
What is surprising is that there are fewer moments of this type than you expect (to be concrete there are only three).
The result is quite like this because this element does not risk to hinder and is placed, in the context described above, in the elements that embellish the game.
The driving pattern is in the tradition of previous games.
Which means that currently there is nothing extraordinary but we can not say that it is negative.
As for the realistic simulation you will have to look elsewhere.
But although we can find better in the competition the driving model goes very well with the type of design of the races.
So everything is ok.
Problems begin to appear after a while.
Unlike the driving model, the collision model is not yet complete.
We don't expect this game to be a complicated warp and collisions, but when you don't have, during a collision with any object, the slightest idea of how your car behaves, so it's not completely good.
During tight overtaking you sometimes touch each other slightly but otherwise your car goes into crazy turns.
Or it ends up in crumbs.
Thanks to the reboot system this is not really a problem but it really annoys you.
The restart is done in such a way that when you have broken your figure or you have gone out in the scenery the game takes you back to the moment of the last point on the route.
But you only have 5 restarts.
When you have used the 5 restarts you have to start the game from the beginning.
So it's more of a tool, in case something doesn't go right, than something you can really rely on.
Sometimes the restarts do not help and you have to find the solution by remembering the piece of itinerary in question.
The great thing about this game is that the same actions end up in the same places.
For example, there are certain turns that you have to pass in a certain way otherwise it does not pass.
Otherwise you encounter on a given place "civilian" vehicles always in the same configuration as you arrived first, fifth, 5 seconds early or a minute late.
What makes you angry are the situations when you see the opponent easily pass between two cars coming in the opposite direction and when you arrive, you have to either stand aside and bypass them or brake.
It doesn't matter if you go to meet him because it is "calculated" in such a way that for the given situation it always arrives very close to your nose.
The opponents have other advantages.
During all the time of the game, you, you arrive in certain places, again without worrying about the time, and you always have the same opponent that precedes you in the same place.
This annoys the most at the end of the game when you ride on a long deck in the opposite direction.
The opponent must pass in front of you at all costs.
When it passes in front of you it hides the view of other vehicles in the opposite direction and you collide a lot of times.
It can be understood that the purpose of this game is to make something captivating and full of adrenaline,but it is clear that you get bored quickly.
And it's a shame because through a simple driving model the game is interesting and the places with so much action that you don't have time to follow everything that happens.
And it doesn’t matter if it’s because of the concept of 50 unique routes, that the order of the races is such that there is no chance of getting bored or something else.
The original idea is to change the car during the races.
You should pay attention to gas pumps on the routes because you can change cars there but most of the time the one you have is enough for you.
Cars are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are ideal for cities, large American displacements for straight highways and super sports cars with exotic outfits on very technical driving for example on lace roads in the mountains.
And the challenge mode, which are races in particular places that you know from the adventure, goes very well with the main diet of the story.
You receive not only medals but also experience points that add to your profile that is common to challenges and adventure.
When you have reached the highest level of driver, different objects begin to unlock:
It connects online with the Autolog function which among other things compares your results with those of other players and provides you with other functions in the community.
One of the most difficult moves to understand is the situation of the last race of the adventure.
You arrive with your car in the subway tunnel (it looks) where you drive in the dark on the tracks (it looks).
Your speed indicator tells you between 150 and 200 km/h (a priori) and behind you arrives a subway train that sends you the car directly to the scrap.
In writing we had a discussion for a few days about whether someone really thought when creating this game or whether the authors really take us for fools.
The technical part of the game is not extra,but the visual part is generally pleasant and in some cases really great.
What is troubling is that in more extreme situations, the imaging does not hold up and in some cases tragically.
This applies especially to accidents with a large number of participants when fluid imaging is no longer useful to you.
The sound part is good and the track is to choose from.
In order to please the most and especially the young audience a new soundtrack has been created in the style "I mix everything", but one can expect that no one will buy the game for the music.
Need for Speed: The Run is a great game.
If the game did not have these stupid mistakes we could say without fear that this is the best production of NFS in recent years.
But this game gives the impression of not being finished.
The fun is really good but be prepared for mistakes to hit you in the eye with the force of an aerodrome reflector.
The Velvet Students in concert with the choirs of Charles University
The Festa Academica festival offers for the third time festivities that connect the International Student Day with the anniversary of the Velvet Revolution with a musical part.
During the festival there are 20 choirs from upper and secondary schools.
The highlight of the festival is two concerts on November 17.
"Charles University has an important part to play in this festival."
"Among the choirs there is the Choir of the Faculty of Pedagogy and Humanities, in the committee of the festival seat the rector Vaclav Hampl," says the leader of the organizing team Jakub Calou.
The highlight of the festival is the concert of the Choir of High Schools and Secondary Classes which takes place with free admission on November 17 from 2 pm on the space located in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
On the program is the composition of the well-known Czech jazzman Karel Ruzicka, Celebration Jazz mass.
In the evening there is the concert "Velvet students" in the premises of the National House in Vinohrady during which the choirs of the higher schools as well as that of Charles University are performed.
The aim of the Festa Academica is not only to celebrate with dignity the International Students’ Day and to commemorate the 22nd anniversary of the Velvet Revolution, but also to present to the public a choir music of the highest level and to develop the creative cooperation of young people.
The main organizer is the Union of Czech Choirs in cooperation with the Jan Kepler High School.
All the action is under the aegis of Bohuslav Svoboda, Mayor of Prague and Vaclav Hampl, Rector of Charles University.
The festival takes place from 16 to 20 November in Prague and Pardubice.
The program offers high-level concerts, music meetings, a student happening and other activities.
Interested parties will find all the information on the web pages of the festival www.festaacademica.cz.
Vicenova, Ambassador to the European Union:
Czechs Behave Like Negatives and Eurosceptics
"The Lisbon Treaty has radically removed the balance between the institutions"
“I didn’t expect such a hard war.”
"It will take 5.6 years before the situation calms down and all the players get used to their new role," Milena Vicenova began her presentation at the Faculty of Law the Czech ambassador to the European Union.
When she managed to describe the different EU bodies and their relations in such an understandable and visible way, to the point that a large number of lecturers at Charles University Law School might envy her, she showed how seriously she takes her motto "understandable and openly about Europe" very seriously.
Vicenova paid tribute to the work of Herman Van Rompuye, the new Permanent President of the European Council.
"From the beginning, there was a resounding criticism that he is faded, that he is a leather roundabout, that he can't fulfill any mission and I have to say that he has taken everyone's breath away because he plays his part perfectly."
"He is a man who knows how to listen to 27 member states, communicates well with them and has a clear vision of the direction to take of Europe."
She explained the new post of the High Representative for Foreign Affairs and Defence Policy as part of an answer to the question: "Who is who in the European Union?" "Which phone number should I call?", thus as an important step towards the uniqueness and greater legibility of the Union's policy towards states, such as China or India.
Nobody wants to forbid us our syrecky (cooked cheese that smells very strong)
Mrs Vicenova also referred to the agenda that the European Council has lived, lives and will live in the near future.
She called the Czech presidency two years ago a success.
The Czechs have solved the rising financial crisis, the gas crisis or have organized an Eastern Partnership Summit.
It called the fall of the government very negative and damaged the image of the Czech Republic.
The Czech representation in the EU is currently very busy.
In the words of the Ambassador, "activity has been at its peak" not only for the Presidency but also for the financial crisis that continues to be resolved even now.
In addition, the new septimal budget of the Union must be approved, which is becoming very complicated due to the current economic situation.
As it would seem that the budget will be slim and in view of savings, which branch will have priority, which countries will be helped the most, the least, everything is to be resolved in the framework of future negotiations.
The Ambassador recalled her slogans with which she arrived in Brussels "For an understandable Europe".
“I really don’t like abbreviations, foreign words, jargon that nobody understands.
As the citizen must understand, it is true that in Brussels no one makes round or twisted pickles, bananas differently large or that no one has forbidden us to make syrecky.
She wants to make better use of the EU environment and see more Czechs in the EU institutions.
A multi-speed Europe awaits us
According to the Ambassador, the Czechs have a reputation for being Eurosceptics and people who only see things in their negative aspect more than positively.
Moreover, she is sorry to see such a small Czech representation in the European institutions.
The fault, according to her, stems from several factors, such as the shyness of our candidates, their inability to write a cover letter and little support from the Czech side.
In addition to a successful Czech presidency, she then underlined the strength and cooperation of the Visegrad Group.
"Believe me, when the Pole, the Magyar, the Slovak come to me, this Frenchman says to me: 'Hey, what are you doing there, what is this Visegrad group still doing?' and he is not happy at all."
According to Vicenova, in the near future, new tough fiscal policy rules await the member countries.
It is the concept of a two-speed, if not multi-speed Europe that prevails rather than a "new European Federation".
"We have countries in the euro area and others outside the euro area."
“We have the Schengen area, we also have the institute for enhanced cooperation.”
In the first place it was said that the countries that want it and those that do not want it remain in their corners.
"There will be a lot of institutes of this type and there will be a really two-speed Europe," Vicenova said.
From this point of view, she also appreciated the mission of the Czech Republic and Herman Van Rompuye to determine the basis on which all issues having an impact on the EU should be debated among all EU members and not only members of the eurozone.
History of a brand:
IBM Innovator Begins Second Century of His Existence
If someone were to search for the word that most closely expresses IBM's strategy, the closest would be "the long term."
For a large public IBM is the symbol of the technological revolution, is a company felt as very current and yet since its creation it has been a hundred years.
The foundation for this long-term strategy was laid by the firm’s first chief executive, visionary Thomas J. Watson Sr.
He left this slogan that a large number of global problems can be solved as long as people are willing to think.
His slogan "THINK!" became the imprint around which the life of a future giant will develop (and also the title of the internal magazine that IBM began publishing in 1935).
This was the basis of Watson's carefully crafted corporate culture.
For us IBM means a long-term thought of continuous movements directed towards the future.
IBM has survived a hundred years thanks to the fact that it has always remained true to its core values and yet has not been afraid to change everyone else around it.
This has enabled us during our first century to transform technology, business and society.
We hope that in the second century we will reach even more"said for the anniversary the current director of the firm Samuel J. Palmisano.
A well-prepared system
Watson, in the 1930s, took care of his employees like Bata in the Czech Republic - IBM people were the only ones among the first American employees to have paid vacation, employer-paid insurance plus a stylish employee uniform and a well-crafted system of rewards for inventors and merchants.
Similarly, IBM has a well-developed customer relationship system.
The company was initially great at discovering talent – as one of the first firms to have abolished all forms of discrimination and thus had a choice.
The current plan is completely in the spirit of the anti-discrimination strategy since it will be a woman – Virginia Rometty – who should replace Palmisano at the head of IBM.
She has worked at IBM for 30 years and is currently Head of Sales, Marketing and Strategy.
IBM in recent years has been doing what is called jamy, online brain-storming from which many future strategies and innovations have come.
No wonder he has a lot of ideas - in the firm there are nearly 500,000 people working.
An institution with a good name
It is the internal and external image of the company that ensures it a secure position in the business field.
“In the beginning, IBM had a concept of an institution rather than a technology firm,” said Rosabeth Moss Kanter, professor of economics at Harvard School of Economics and author of the book on IBM.
