So was the work of the person from Cali who identified the corpse of Alfonso Cano
A typewriter from Cali went down in history as the man who confirmed the death of "Alfonso Cano".
The work of these officials is crucial.
On November 4, a typewriter of the Cali CTI went down in history as the person who confirmed the identity of the supreme leader of the FARC: "Alfonso Cano", by confronting his fingerprints.
Of the seven typists who work in the local offices of the CTI, this week it was the turn of "availability" of Eliazar González, a man from Puerto Tejada who has been working for 21 years in the field of judicial investigation.
At the beginning of his career, González worked in the municipalities of Chocó, where many times he had to spend more than five days in the forest to get to the place where the bodies that had to be identified were located.
In 2000 he moved to the capital of Valle and after taking appropriate courses, he specialized in typoscopy, which is the study of friction skin, i.e. the palms and feet.
During the week of the operation against alias Alfonso Cano, Eliazar was warned to take with him clothes for at least three days.
Something very big was waiting for him.
On Friday night he left for Cauca in a helicopter from Palmira.
He knew that he had to identify two bodies and that one of them was suspected to be the man who ran the world's oldest guerrilla, so he was asked to take the card with the ten fingerprints of Guillermo León Sáenz (his real name).
But when he arrived with the investigative team at the location of the corpse, he did not recognize it by its physical appearance, because it was very different from the one he had seen in the media.
He had no beard, he was dressed like a local peasant, without glasses and much thinner.
But the fingerprints aren't lying.
Accompanied by a galtonian magnifying glass, ink, a sampler and a lantern, Eliazar compared the fingerprints of the corpse with those of the card.
His eye did not deceive him: it was "Alfonso Cano".
That same night, the man from Puerto Tejada was the official who confirmed to Defense Minister Juan Carlos Pinzón that yes, he was the supreme leader of the FARC.
In Search of the Footprint
For a typewriter from Sijín de Cali, the recognition that President Juan Manuel Santos gave to Eliazar González, in a press conference for the operation against "Cano", is very significant.
A lot of people don’t know our work.
Dactyloscopy is an exact science, with no margin for error, that can be crucial in resolving crimes.
Apart from identifying the bodies, typists support investigations for crimes such as theft and homicide and confirm the identities of those captured.
When captured, many offenders present fake ID cards or do not have documents.
We take their fingerprints and search the database.
The researcher said that in a case of theft he had to remove part of the wall of a house, because in this place the thief had pressed his hand to bring out a safe full of jewelry and money.
"The walls are difficult because they are not adequate areas to take a fingerprint, but in this case we were able to get the fingerprint with the whole hand and identify the offender who had participated in different robberies," he recalls.
Fingerprints can also dismiss or confirm suspects in homicide cases.
Recently we found a dead man, with drink bottles around him.
Through the investigation it was determined that a relative may be a suspect in the crime and indeed a fingerprint on the bottle coincided.
Even if it doesn't guarantee that he's the killer, it puts him on the scene.
A CTI typewriter explained that "fingerprints are extracted from objects with chemical or physical reagents."
When they appear, a picker or strip is used to pick them up.
Subsequently, the fingerprints are sent to Asif, the database of declinants, or to the National Civil Registry.
“The problem is that there are still a lot of undocumented Colombians,” the CTI expert said.
He explained that everything is not as shown in the CSI television program.
As everything that shines is not gold, everything that is touched does not necessarily become a footprint.
It can, however, be used, if the necessary confrontation is carried out.
